3366 if ( ! (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) )
3367 YY_NEW_FILE;
3368 }
3369 break;
3370 }
3371
3372 case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
3373 (yy_c_buf_p) =
3374 (yytext_ptr) + yy_amount_of_matched_text;
3375
3376 yy_current_state = yy_get_previous_state( );
3377
3378 yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
3379 yy_bp = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ;
3380 goto yy_match;
3381
3382 case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
3383 (yy_c_buf_p) =
3384 &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)];
3385
3386 yy_current_state = yy_get_previous_state( );
3387
3388 yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
3389 yy_bp = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ;
3390 goto yy_find_action;
3391 }
3392 break;
3393 }
3394
3395 default:
3396 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
3397 "fatal flex scanner internal error--no action found" );
3398 } /* end of action switch */
3399 } /* end of scanning one token */
3400 } /* end of user's declarations */
3401} /* end of yylex */

3403/* yy_get_next_buffer - try to read in a new buffer
3404 *
3405 * Returns a code representing an action:
3406 * EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH -
3407 * EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN - continue scanning from current position
3408 * EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE - end of file
3409 */
3410static int yy_get_next_buffer (void)
3411{
3412 char *dest = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf;
3413 char *source = (yytext_ptr);
3414 yy_size_t number_to_move, i;
3415 int ret_val;
3416
3417 if ( (yy_c_buf_p) > &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars) + 1] )
3418 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
3419 "fatal flex scanner internal error--end of buffer missed" );
3420
3421 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_fill_buffer == 0 )
3422 { /* Don't try to fill the buffer, so this is an EOF. */
3423 if ( (yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr) - YY_MORE_ADJ == 1 )
3424 {
3425 /* We matched a single character, the EOB, so
3426 * treat this as a final EOF.
3427 */
3428 return EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
3429 }
3430
3431 else
3432 {
3433 /* We matched some text prior to the EOB, first
3434 * process it.
3435 */
3436 return EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
3437 }
3438 }
3439
3440 /* Try to read more data. */
3441
3442 /* First move last chars to start of buffer. */
3443 number_to_move = (yy_size_t) ((yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr)) - 1;
3444
3445 for ( i = 0; i < number_to_move; ++i )
3446 *(dest++) = *(source++);
3447
3448 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status == YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING )
3449 /* don't do the read, it's not guaranteed to return an EOF,
3450 * just force an EOF
3451 */
3452 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars) = 0;
3453
3454 else
3455 {
3456 int num_to_read =
3457 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
3458
3459 while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
3460 { /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */
3461
3462 /* just a shorter name for the current buffer */
3463 YY_BUFFER_STATE b = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE;
3464
3465 int yy_c_buf_p_offset =
3466 (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - b->yy_ch_buf);
3467
3468 if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
3469 {
3470 int new_size = b->yy_buf_size * 2;
3471
3472 if ( new_size <= 0 )
3473 b->yy_buf_size += b->yy_buf_size / 8;
3474 else
3475 b->yy_buf_size *= 2;
3476
3477 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *)
3478 /* Include room in for 2 EOB chars. */
3479 yyrealloc((void *) b->yy_ch_buf,(yy_size_t) (b->yy_buf_size + 2) );
3480 }
3481 else
3482 /* Can't grow it, we don't own it. */
3483 b->yy_ch_buf = NULL;
3484
3485 if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
3486 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
3487 "fatal error - scanner input buffer overflow" );
3488
3489 (yy_c_buf_p) = &b->yy_ch_buf[yy_c_buf_p_offset];
3490
3491 num_to_read = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size -
3492 number_to_move - 1;
3493
3494 }
3495
3496 if ( num_to_read > YY_READ_BUF_SIZE )
3497 num_to_read = YY_READ_BUF_SIZE;
3498
3499 /* Read in more data. */
3500 YY_INPUT( (&YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move]),
3501 (yy_n_chars), num_to_read );
3502
3503 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
3504 }
3505
3506 if ( (yy_n_chars) == 0 )
3507 {
3508 if ( number_to_move == YY_MORE_ADJ )
3509 {
3510 ret_val = EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
3511 yyrestart(yyin );
3512 }
3513
3514 else
3515 {
3516 ret_val = EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
3517 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status =
3518 YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING;
3519 }
3520 }
3521
3522 else
3523 ret_val = EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN;
3524
3525 if ((int) ((yy_n_chars) + number_to_move) > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size) {
3526 /* Extend the array by 50%, plus the number we really need. */
3527 int new_size = (yy_n_chars) + number_to_move + ((yy_n_chars) >> 1);
3528 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyrealloc((void *) YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf,(yy_size_t) new_size );
3529 if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
3530 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_get_next_buffer()" );
3531 }
3532
3533 (yy_n_chars) += number_to_move;
3534 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
3535 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars) + 1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
3536
3537 (yytext_ptr) = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[0];
3538
3539 return ret_val;
3540}

4421static void
4422comment (void)
4423{
4424 int c;
4425
4426 while (1)
4427 {
4428 c = input();
4429 while (c != '*' && c != EOF)
4430 {
4431 if (c == '\n')
4432 lineno++;
4433 c = input();
4434 }
4435
4436 if (c == '*')
4437 {
4438 c = input();
4439 while (c == '*')
4440 c = input();
4441 if (c == '/')
4442 break; /* found the end */
4443 }
4444
4445 if (c == '\n')
4446 lineno++;
4447
4448 if (c == EOF)
4449 {
4450 einfo (_("%F%P: EOF in comment\n"));
4451 break;
4452 }
4453 }
